Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, low CO₂, and significant proteinuria, suggesting impaired renal function with possible metabolic acidosis. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal, high protein, bilirubin, ketones, and glucose) further support renal dysfunction, possibly with tubular involvement. No evidence of urinary infection. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation and further assessment for underlying renal pathology.
